content:
Create a remote connection using the Microsoft Azure SQL Database connector to sync data from Microsoft Azure SQL Database to CRM Analytics.

On the Data Manager Connections tab, click New Connection. Click the name of the connector and click Next. Enter the connector settings:

* Connection Name: Identifies the connections.
* Developer Name: API name for the connection.
* Description: Description
* Database: Microsoft Azure SQL database name.
* JDBC Connection URL: URL schema for the database.
* Username: User name for the database login.
* Password: Password for the database login.

To filter data synced to CRM Analytics, exclude unnecessary or sensitive data by creating a data sync filter. Filters run on the source object and speed up data sync.

Filters can be used with the Microsoft Azure SQL Database connector. The syntax is described in the Azure SQL Database and WHERE documentation.

When working with this connector, keep these behaviors in mind:

* Connected object names must start with a letter and contain only letters, digits, or underscores.
* This connector can sync up to 100 million rows or 50 GB per object.
* Salesforce Government Cloud org data is protected in transit with advanced encryption and can sync up to 10 million rows or 5 GB for each connected object.

There's a new codebase version of this connector available. See the release note for information on the connection upgrade path and considerations when creating connections.
title: Connecting Microsoft Azure SQL Database to CRM Analytics
